<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-4117] org.codehaus.groovy.runtime.metaclass.MetaClassRegistryImpl#registerMethods should not call System.exit</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-4117</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;After an unexpected exit from our app, I saw that org.codehaus.groovy.runtime.metaclass.MetaClassRegistryImpl#registerMethods has an System.exit routine.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We are using groovy from within our Java application. It actually killed our app due to a configuration issue.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The groovy engine should throw an exception not System.exit.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I suggest to review all System.exit calls and replace them with throwing an exception.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
